Name: Country Cottage Wall

Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate a quaint, rural look.

※Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.
Name: Country House Wall

Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate a quaint, rural look.

※Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.
Name: Country Mansion Wall

Description: A decadent array of carefully stacked glasses, sure to impress guests at parties...as long as they don't come crashing down. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10) VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12) Gear Durability Bonus: +3 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Wine Coupe Tower

Description:
This decorative winged object evokes Valigarmanda's elemental prowess and perilous wrath.

※One per estate only.
Name: Skyruin Trophy

Description:
Twin blades that tell a story of ambition, domination, and loss.

※One per estate only.
Name: Resilient Sword Stand

Description: This wooden cabinet has a near-infinite capacity for storing utensils and knickknacks. Makes an excellent partition due to its imposing size and sturdy construction.
Name: Kitchen Cabinet

Description: Now cluttered with an ever-present collection of household odds and ends, this chair's transformation from seat to shelf was a gradual affair.
Name: Slovenly Chair

Description: Although equally endearing, this stuffed ornament is considerably less slimy than its live counterpart.
Name: Stuffed Axolotl Eft

Description: Modeled after a certain reindeer calf, this plush toy thankfully lacks the real Flag's prodigious appetite.
Name: Stuffed Flag

Description: Crafted to resemble a splishy-wishy young nixie, and infused with levitation magicks, this whimsical plushie floats like a balloon.
Name: Fluffy-wuffy Stuffed Drippy

Description: A cuddly punutiy lovingly rendered in fluffy fabric.
Name: Stuffed Punutiy

Description: A window crafted to resemble a Hingan-style sliding door.
Name: Decorative Hingan Door

Description: An imitation skylight with illusory properties. Gaze upwards to appreciate this portal to a striking crimson sky.
Name: Sunset Phasmascape

Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays a breathtaking view of the Goblet in all its splendor.
Name: Goblet Phasmascape

Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays a picturesque cluster of hillside houses at the Lavender Beds.
Name: Lavender Beds Phasmascape

Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the community of Mist and the stunning stretch of coastline it sits atop.
Name: Mist Phasmascape

Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the vibrant rooves and tree-topped outcrops of Shirogane.
Name: Shirogane Phasmascape

Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the ornate, pointed spires that punctuate the Empyreum skyline.
Name: Empyreum Phasmascape

Description: A simple, functional table. The two-tiered design opens up a wealth of storage possibilities.
Name: Twintop Table

Description: A mug brimming with deliciously sweet, velvety hot cocoa. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10) VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12) Gear Durability Bonus: +3 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Mug of Cocoa

Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Everkeep fashion.

※Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.
Name: Everkeep Striking Dummy

Description: Replete with seating, this elevated wooden platform affords an unparalleled view of the firmament. For the astrologer who prizes comfort as much as the pursuit of heavenly knowledge.
Name: Stargazing Deck

Description: A perfectly plain wooden gate that provides passage to your property.
Name: Wooden Garden Gate

Description: An arcanely complicated feather possessed of three conflicting elemental energies.
Name: Ruinous Plume

Description: A piece of gear that became fused to the scales of Zoraal Ja, King of Resolve.
Name: Resilient Armor
